Peter Churchyard writes:
|> There is another side to this.. If you just want to verify the signature on
|> a message then you need to have a cert for the sender signed by someone you
|> trust. In PEM there is a strict Hierachy that means that you only have to
|> have a few top certs to validate the sigs of all PEM mail (IPRA and PCA's)
|> 
|> PGP does suffer from this lack of structure.

this is not a bug, it's a feature.  because pgp does not rely on
a strict hierarchy of certifying authorities, pgp users can define
their own trust models.

	peter
